Package: pmatools
Title: Pairwise Meta-Analysis with GRADE Certainty Assessment
Version: 0.3.0
Authors@R: person("Yuki", "Furukawa", email = "furukawa.y.psy@gmail.com",
                  role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: End-to-end pairwise meta-analysis pipeline with GRADE certainty
    assessment, Summary of Findings table, and reproducible export bundle.
    Wraps the {meta} package for data ingestion (long/wide), random- or
    common-effect pooling, contour-enhanced funnel plots with Egger's test,
    and auto-laid-out forest plots. GRADE follows the BMJ 2025 Core GRADE
    series (Guyatt et al.): Risk of Bias (BMJ Fig 2 weight-based dominance
    plus inflation threshold), Inconsistency (BMJ Fig 2 flowchart with MID
    threshold for clinical decision), Indirectness (manual), Imprecision
    (CI vs null + Optimal Information Size from MID), and Publication Bias
    (Egger / unpublished-studies flowchart). Outputs SoF flextable, multi-
    outcome GRADE table, and Appendix report (docx/html/pdf/md), and
    bundles everything plus a reproducible analysis.R into a ZIP archive.
